VLib

All-round header-only c++ library.

Language Dialect

VLib is developed for the language dialect c++20.

Operating Systems

VLib supports operating systems macos & linux.

Limits

Numeric limits structure.
template <typename Type> 
struct vlib::limits

Template parameters

typename
Type
Required

Examples

#include <vlib/types.h>
int int_max = vlib::limits<int>::max;

Range

Iterate a certain range.
template <typename Iter = Forwards, typename Type = ullong> 
struct vlib::Range

Template parameters

typename
Iter
typename
Type

Examples

#include <vlib/types.h>

// Iterate from 0 till 1000000.
for (auto& i: vlib::Range(1000000)) { ... }

// Iterate from 0 till 100.
for (auto& i: vlib::Range(0, 100)) { ... }

// Safe while loop.
auto x = vlib::Range(0, 10);
while (++x) { ... }

// Iterate from 1000000 till 0.
for (auto& i: vlib::Range<vlib::Backwards>(1000000)) { ... }

// Iterate from 100 till 0.
for (auto& i: vlib::Range<vlib::Backwards>(100, 0)) { ... }

// Warning!
// This causes an infinite loop.
while (++vlib::Range(0, 10)) { ... }

Exception

Exception type.

Define preprocessor variable vlib_enable_trace to enable a stacktrace.
Define preprocessor variable vlib_trace_depth to set a max stacktrace depth, the default is 32.
The stacktrace only works properly when the program is compiled without optimization.
struct vlib::Exception

Examples

#include <vlib/types.h>
vlib::Exception x (...);

Pipe

Pipe type.
struct vlib::Pipe

Examples

#include <vlib/types.h>

// Dump to the stdout console.
vlib::out << "Hello World! \n";

// Dump to the stderr console.
vlib::err << "Error: ... \n";

// Create a class that can be dumped using "Pipe".
class myclass {
    constexpr
    const char* c_str() const {
        return "Hello World!";
    }
    friend
    auto& operator <<(vlib::Pipe& pipe, const myclass& obj) {
        return pipe << obj.c_str();
    }
};

Power of

Calculate the power of with a numeric.

Function pow_r updates the current object, while pow creates a copy.

Parameter x can be negative when the numeric is floating. The power of will than act as a division. For example Double(10.0).pow(-1) will return 0.1. The underlying formula is numeric / pow(abs(numeric), (-x)+1).

ullong max_len = 0;

Thread

Thread type.

Can be used to use as a base class for another type.

Can be used to start a thread function.
template <typename Derived = vlib::Null> 
struct vlib::Thread

Template parameters

typename
Derived

Notes

- The thread acts as a shared pointer.

Examples

// --------------------------------------------------------
// Thread class.

#include <vlib/types.h>

// Create a thread class.
struct some_thread : public vlib::Thread<some_thread> {
    
    // The thread run function.
    void*  run(void) {
        vlib::print("Starting thread: ", id()));
    return NULL;
}

};

int main() {
some_thread thread;
thread.start();
thread.join();
return 0;
}

// --------------------------------------------------------
// Thread function.

#include <vlib/types.h>

// A thread function without args.
void* some_func(void*) {
vlib::print("Hello World!");
return NULL;
}

// The thread function.
void* some_func_with_args(vlib::String day, vlib::String name) {
vlib::print("Good ", day, " ", name, "!");
return NULL;
}

int main() {

// Start a thread without arguments.
vlib::FThread thread0;
thread0.start(some_func);
thread0.join();

// Start a thread with arguments.
vlib::FThread thread1;
thread1.start(some_func_with_args, "Sunday", "World");
thread1.join();

return 0;

}

Thread Pool

Thread Pool type.

Currently only supports function threads.
struct vlib::ThreadPool

Examples

// ---------------------------------------------------------
// Standard thread pool.

// Include.
#include <vlib/types.h>

// A thread function.
void* some_func(const Int& i) {
    vlib::print("Running thread: ", i, ".");
    return NULL;
}

int main() {
    
    // Start a thread without arguments.
    vlib::ThreadPool thread_pool(25); // maximum 25 threads.
    
    // Iterate threads.
    Int index = 0;
    for (auto& thread: thread_pool) {
        thread.start(some_func, index);
        ++index;
    }
    for (auto& thread: thread_pool) {
        thread.join();
    }
    return 0;
    
}

// ---------------------------------------------------------
// Managed thread pool.
// The current example creates 100 threads.
// But only 25 will be running simultaneously.

// Include.
#include <vlib/types.h>

// A thread function.
void* some_func(const Int& i) {
    vlib::print("Running thread: ", i, ".");
    return NULL;
}

int main() {
    
    // Start a thread without arguments.
    vlib::ThreadPool thread_pool(25); // maximum 25 threads.
    
    // Iterate threads.
    for (auto& index: range(100)) {
        thread_pool.start(somefunc, index);
    }
    return 0;
    
}

Process

Process type.
- By default it executes a bash script / command.
struct vlib::Proc

Examples

#include <vlib/types.h>
vlib::Proc proc0;
if (proc0.execute("echo Hello World!") != 0) { ... }

// Execute a synchronous process.
vlib::Proc proc1 { .async = true };
if (proc1.execute("echo Hello World!") == 0) {
    ...
    if (proc1.join() == 0) {
        ...
    }
}

// The avaiable construct options and their default values.
vlib::Proc proc2 {
    .input = "",
    .input_len = 0,
    .timeout = 15000,
    .async = false,
}

tail

Tail the daemon logs.

- Requires root priviliges.
/
String tail(const Int& lines = 100) {
if (getuid() != 0) {
throw DaemonError("Root privileges required.");
}
if (!m_path.exists()) {
throw DaemonError(tostr("Daemon \"", m_path, "\" does not exist."));
}
String command;
#if OSID == 0
command = tostr("sudo journalctl -u ", m_settings.name, ".service --no-pager -n ", lines);
#elif OSID == 1
throw OSError(tostr("Operating system \"MacOS\" is not yet supported."));
#endif
Proc proc;
if (proc.execute(command) != 0 || proc.exit_status() != 0) {
throw DaemonError("Failed to tail the daemon.");
}
return proc.err_or_out();

Zip

Create or extract a zip archive.

Supports zip archives that exceed 4GB (zip64).

Only supports zip files that are on a single disk.

Only supports the following extra fields.
- ZIP64 extended information extra field.
- Info-ZIP Unix Extra Field (type 2).
All unsupported extra fields are silently ignored.
This class is experimental and still in development.
struct vlib::Zip

Examples

#include <vlib/compression.h>
vlib::Zip zip;
...

Entry

A zip archive file entry.

An entry contains the following attributes:
uint64_t        offset = 0;             // file header offset.
uint16_t        mode = 0;               // file mode directly from assigned "st_mode".
uint16_t        uid = 0;                // uid of the path.
uint16_t        gid = 0;                // gid of the path.
uint16_t        mod_time = 0;           // mod time of the path
uint16_t        mod_date = 0;           // mod date of the path.
uint64_t        compressed_len = 0;     // length of uncompressed data.
uint64_t        uncompressed_len = 0;   // length of compressed data.
uint32_t        crc = 0;                // crc32 checksum.
String          name;                   // sub path.
String          data;                   // compressed data.
.
Member 
struct vlib::Zip::Entry

Examples

vlib::Zip zip;
zip.read("/tmp/archive.zip");
for (auto& entry: zip.entries()) {
    ...
}

File names

Get all the file names from the archive.

The archive must have been initialized by one of the Zip member functions. For example read().
It is much faster to iterate the entries with entries(). Since file_names() creates a copy of each file name.
Member 
constexpr 
Array<String> vlib::Zip::file_names() { ... }

Return

Array
The return type is Array.

Examples

// Read a zip archive.
vlib::Zip zip;
zip.read("/tmp/archive.zip");

// Iterate the files names.
// Not recommended since it copies each file name.
for (auto& name: zip.file_names()) {
    print(name);
}

// Recommended version:
for (auto& entry: zip.entries()) {
    print(entry.name);
}
